.TH "setLocation" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
setLocation \- modify the location information of nodes in the cluster
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]SdbDC.setLocation(<hostName>, <location>, [options])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDC
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to modify the location information of nodes on the
specified host in the cluster.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
hostName ( \f[I]string, required\f[] )
.PP
The hostname to modify location information for.
The specified hostname needs to exist in the current cluster, and the location
information of all nodes on this host will be modified.
.PP
location ( \f[I]string, required\f[] )
.PP
New location information.
.IP \[bu] 2
The maximum length of location information is limited to 256 bytes
.IP \[bu] 2
When the value is an empty string, it means to delete the location information
of nodes on the specified host
.PP
options ( \f[I]object, optional\f[] )
.PP
Specify filter conditions through the parameter "options":
.IP \[bu] 2
Domain ( \f[I]string | string array\f[] ): Filter by domain, only operate on
data groups belonging to the specified domain(s).
A single domain name or an array of domain names can be specified
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]Domain: "mydomain"\f[] or
\f[C]Domain: ["domain1", "domain2"]\f[]
.RE
